metadata.description:
PYROMAN/DESIRE/BURNING BUILDING - 

Every day, from the window of his rented apartment, he watches an ugly old building. Every day he imagines how it burns. Every day he imagines setting it on fire, pouring gasoline on it under the cover of night. Obsessive thoughts do not leave him every day. And then one day, in the window of his apartment, he saw this old building, it was Completely engulfed in fire. 
Now its meaning is lost.  
He lost himself along with the missed opportunity and the building burning at his hands. He missed the chance. 

Goodbye, unknown pyromaniac!
